Welcome to my website!

PhD Eng. Academic Researcher at AGH University of Krakow Lecturer Founder of Institute for Sustainable Energy

I am an environmentally-oriented analytical researcher at AGH University of Krakow, Poland. My expertise lies in the fields of chemical and environmental engineering, with a focus on studying how energy generation processes affect the environment and air quality. Currently, my work centers on applying AI-based data science to tackle environmental challenges. I am concerned particularly on particulate matter in atmoshere, solid particles emission and fate of persistent organic pollutants.

I am also the founder of the Research Group of Data Science and Advanced Analytics, which brings together experts to explore innovative solutions in data science, machine learning, and advanced analytics, all with a focus on promoting environmental sustainability.

Feel free to explore my research, projects, and the exciting work we are doing at the Research Group!
